        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 9:01AM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 901 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Truxton to Berkshire. Movement was east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 30 to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cortland, Norwich, Plymouth, North Norwich, Greene, Oxford,
Sherburne, Richford, Solon, and Cincinnatus.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
